				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Question:
<br />

<br />
I'm tired of e-mail notifications. What can I do?
<br />

<br />
Answer:
<br />

<br />
Don't worry! Deleting e-mails is much simpler than deleting forum postings. But here are a pair of suggestions.
<br />

<br />
The best way is to register bbAntiSpam.
<br />

<br />
A good approach is to automatically move e-mails to a mail client folder. You can filter either by a mail header, either by the &quot;from&quot; field.
<br />

<br />
1) by a mail header
<br />

<br />
bbAntiSpam notifications contains the following mail header:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">X-bbAniSpam-spam: Yes</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
If your software supports filtering by a mail header, use this way.
<br />

<br />
2) by the &quot;from&quot; field
<br />

<br />
If your board email is something like &quot;phpbb@my.site&quot;, then bbAntiSpam sends e-mails with the following &quot;From&quot; address:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">bbAntiSpam &lt;phpbb@my.site&gt;</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td class="spaceRow" colspan="2" height="1"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/spacer.gif" alt="" width="1" height="1" /></td>
	</tr>
</table>

